The paper discusses a cognitive radio scheme that exploits spatial dimensions to minimize interference and increase system throughput. This involves techniques such as multi-user diversity, interference alignment, and MIMO channels. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IT (Information Theory), which deals with the transmission, processing, and utilization of information. Other likely sub-categories include cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.MM (Multimedia), and cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science), which all involve aspects of communication, networking, and signal processing.
